{
  "texts": [
    "Considerable shifts in student profiles were observed across three sessions, which may indicate the influence of the AI-integration strategies on how students interacted with ChatGPT.",
    "In the first session, students predominantly relied on AI for generating code with minimal engagement in the problem-solving process, which aligns with previous findings that students had tendency to use AI tools to get direct solutions (Ghimire & Edwards, 2024; Sun et al., 2024).",
    "However, after the training session focused on effective ChatGPT usage and prompting skills in the second session, a significant transformation was noted in their interaction patterns.",
    "That is, many students began not only to use AI to generate code but also to refine and critically evaluate the AI's outputs to align the solutions more closely with the task requirements.",
    "Similarly, in the third session in which students were provided with a guide document involving sample examples and prompts, students who initially relied heavily on AI for code generation, as well as those who refined AI-generated code or used AI for assistance, increasingly moved towards more collaborative interactions with AI."
  ]
}